    "Furthermore, existing research is highly concentrated on Java and Python languages, which limits the applicability of our conclusions to system-level languages like C++ and Rust or other dynamically typed languages.",
    "Therefore, conclusions regarding cross-language generalization capabilities should be viewed as provisional.Threats from Technical Timeliness and Model Opacity.",
    "Technical evolution and model black-boxes constitute unique threats.",
    "Given the rapid iteration of LLM technology (such as the leap from GPT-3.5 to GPT-4o), the performance metrics of specific models may quickly become obsolete.",
    "Furthermore, the opacity of closed-source commercial models (e.g., updates to training data) may lead to the irreproducibility of experimental results."
